T1  - Success in Management Consulting and the Concept of Eliteness Motivation
AU  - Miner, John B.
Y1  - 1971/09/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255080
DO  - 10.5465/255080
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 367
EP  - 378
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Two hypotheses regarding the sources of success in management consulting are investigated using biographical data in a predictive design. The hypotheses deal with: (1) a total life pattern of successful endeavor, and (2) a maximal prior exposure to top management culture. The data only partially support the hypotheses. Rather, the concept of elite-ness motivation seems most adequate to explain the results obtained.
AB  - Two hypotheses regarding the sources of success in management consulting are investigated using biographical data in a predictive design. The hypotheses deal with: (1) a total life pattern of successful endeavor, and (2) a maximal prior exposure to top management culture. The data only partially support the hypotheses. Rather, the concept of elite-ness motivation seems most adequate to explain the results obtained.
