N2  - The article reports the author's opinions regarding the accessibility of business education in the U.S. The author focuses on the availability of business education courses to residents of inner-city ghettos. It is suggested that business teachers and university administrators take socioeconomic factors into consideration when planning a business curriculum for minority groups living in the inner-city.
