T1  - The Control Structure of Organizations: An Empirical Examination
AU  - McMahon, J. Timothy
AU  - Perritt, G. W.
Y1  - 1971/09/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255077
DO  - 10.5465/255077
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 327
EP  - 340
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Current research on the measurement of ?control? or ?influence? in organizational functioning is critically examined. Theoretical and methodological questions are raised and a revised method of analysis is presented and tested. It is concluded that the degree of concordance of perceptions of the organizational control structure is an important variable, and that the amount and distribution of control are necessary but not sufficient measures in analysis of the control structure.
AB  - Current research on the measurement of ?control? or ?influence? in organizational functioning is critically examined. Theoretical and methodological questions are raised and a revised method of analysis is presented and tested. It is concluded that the degree of concordance of perceptions of the organizational control structure is an important variable, and that the amount and distribution of control are necessary but not sufficient measures in analysis of the control structure.
